      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VIIPURI (4) settled back and did a good job beaten less than 2L over 1100m at Gosford. He's hard-fit and will find this grade more to his liking. The longer sprint will suit and presents on an 8-day return for a top Sydney stable. The local PINK LAMBORGHINI (6) resumes and is proven fresh. She's trialled well here and has the early speed to control the race. Lightly raced with plenty of scope for more improvement. BENAMERA (2) twi starts back winning a 64 over 1400m at Newcastle. That would have him right in it. PLATINUM RIDGE (8) resumed here two weeks ago and dropped right out of contention. A warning was recorded against the gelding's tractability. Won his Maiden in good style second-up last time, and we can see more from him.",
